   - Or leave it unspecified so the general-purpose picker shows all models

5. **`/apps/web/app/admin/settings/page.tsx`** (lines 70-148)
   - Add a new `RoleDef` to `MODEL_ROLES` array with:
     - `settingKey: ROUTE_SETTING_KEYS.vision`
     - `stage: 'vision'` (or `null` to skip stage requirements)
     - `effortSettingKey: REASONING_EFFORT_SETTING_KEYS.vision`
   - Add title, description, etc.

6. **`/apps/web/app/admin/settings/_components/model-picker.tsx`** (no code changes)
   - No changes needed; it already accepts any `settingKey` and `stage`

7. **`/apps/web/app/api/admin/models/route.ts`** (lines 76-115)
   - Add `'vision'` to the `StageOrGeneral` type (line 74)
   - Optionally add `parseStage()` logic to handle `'vision'`
   - Existing pool filtering logic will work unchanged

8. **Any worker that needs vision inference** (create new or modify existing)
   - Call `resolveRouteFromSettings(db, 'vision')`
   - Implement fallback pattern to a hardcoded route

### **Optional files (documentation only):**

- `/.env.example` — already has Google creds configured
- `/docs/oracle/01-model-roles-and-routes.md` — update to mention vision role
- `/packages/db/src/seed.ts` — optionally seed the `default_vision_route` setting

